Package com.paypal.merchant.sdk.domain

Interface Summary
CheckedInClient  
CheckedInMerchantLocation This interface returns various info about the checked in merchant.
ManualEntryCardData ManualEntryCardData When taking a credit card payment where the card is not present this class is used to contain the card data.
MerchantLogo This class is meant to provide the status of the addMerchantLogo and deleteMerhantLogo APIs.
SecureCreditCard Sets of card data that move in/out of the SDK must implement this interface.
TransactionExtras When taking a payment you can specify some extra data that will be stored in the paypal system.

These include the payment due date, the payment terms, the payer's email, the billing and shipping
information, etc.
TransactionRecord This class represents a historical transaction.
 

Class Summary
Address The address object allows the Address info to be formatted and
organized in a way that makes it easier to extract specific info
such as city, state fields - that maybe needed for requests sent
to the backend.
Address.Builder Use this Builder interface to construct the Address object.
BuyerInfo  
DefaultResponseHandler<T,E> This is the base response handler for SDK async responses.
DomainFactory Used to create instances of the interfaces found in com.paypal.merchant.sdk.domain
Merchant The Merchant object is an integral part of the SDK and acts as a single point from which all information about the
merchant is available both to the application and also internally to the SDK.
Although not provided as a parameter explicitly in every API the merchant object is critical to the workings of the
SDK.
PayPalUser  
PPError<T> A base class for errors from the PayPalHere system.
 

Enum Summary
CheckedInClientStatus This enum class describes the status of the checked in client, thus indicating whether he/she would be able to make a payment to the checked in merchant.
Merchant.AvailabilityTypeEnum This enum type indicates the availability status of the merchant, whether he/she is open or closed for business.
Merchant.MobilityTypeEnum This enum type indicates whether the merchant is at a fixed location or is mobile.
PaymentMethod  
PaymentTerms Information about when a payment is due.
PPError.BasicErrors The simplest type of PPError the API might return.
SecureCreditCard.EncryptionMode The type of encryption on this secure credit card.
